				Your guide is lacking. Alot. Do not waste points on pickpockets. spend no more than 5 points an this skill it climbs Quickly while youre fighting orcs and as you will find out your backstab is just short of impossible to maxout. At 18th lvl I am at the top of all my skills exept backstab which is around 15pts down. Now this is important because your skill determines how much damage you do in a successful backstab. As a dark elven rogue my int is way higher than average and I have a very easy time learning trades and skills in general (I mastered in pottery in about an hour and a half realtime) but for whatever reason backstab defies the easy climb to 95 where it should be. My recomendation is to save your practice points and spend them all on bs exept the 1 needed to learn the skill. Your dodge, pp, parry, duel wield, double attack, and safefall will all climb to max in a few levels where as your backstab &quot;the skill rogues are known for&quot; will not. As for merchants not selling to you because your a rogue try the secret hand shake, works every time. <BR>
